<item>
            <title>[LU-17507] MOFED find should use -H in cases where /usr/src/ofa_kernel/default is a symlink</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17507</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;MOFED find should use -H in cases where /usr/src/ofa_kernel/default is a symlink&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A default installation is for /usr/src/ofa_kernel/default to be a symlink, it is also the default place to expect the MOFED kernel development headers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When &apos;find&apos; defaults to never follow symlinks the build breaks due to the &lt;b&gt;expected&lt;/b&gt; MOFED headers not being found when find is searching for the ofed_scripts sub directory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;At a minimum find needs to use -H to ensure the symlinks specified on the command line are followed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
